<h2>Overview</h2><p>If you’ve ever battled with stubborn Jeep doors that refuse to budge, you’re not alone. The struggle of removing doors on a Jeep Wrangler—especially the JK model—can be a common problem made worse by corrosion and wear. Fortunately, TMR Customs offers a practical solution with their Delrin Door Hinge Liners. These bushings not only alleviate the factors causing difficulty but bolster the longevity of your door hinges.</p><h2>What This Covers</h2><p>This article delves into the installation process of TMR Customs’ Delrin Door Hinge Liners, a necessary upgrade for any Jeep owner tired of dealing with the annoyance of stuck doors. We’ll discuss how to effectively replace your old hinge liners, tools you’ll need, and tips for a smooth installation.</p><h2>Step-by-Step Breakdown</h2><ol><li><strong>Prepare for Installation:</strong> Before you begin, you’ll need a few basic tools: a hammer, a punch tool (provided by TMR), and some WD-40 for lubrication. It’s wise to apply WD-40 beforehand to allow it to penetrate and ease the removal of the old liners.</li><li><strong>Removing Old Liners:</strong> Use the punch tool to knock out the old hinge liners. Make sure to protect your Jeep’s paint with cardboard or other materials if needed. For particularly stubborn liners, consider using a flathead screwdriver to coax the edges before applying the punch.</li><li><strong>Cleaning the Hinges:</strong> Once the old liners are out, clean the hinge area thoroughly to remove any corrosion or debris. This step is crucial as any leftover materials can cause interference with the new liners.</li><li><strong>Installing the Delrin Liners:</strong> With the hinges clean and prepared, take your Delrin bushings and push them into place by hand. Unlike the old metal liners, these should fit snugly and easily without the need for a hammer.</li><li><strong>Final Touches:</strong> After installation, check the hinge pins for any corrosion and clean them accordingly. Lubricate moving parts with a lithium-based grease to ensure smooth operation.</li></ol><h2>Helpful Tips</h2><ul><li>Always ensure that the hinge area is clean before inserting new liners to avoid any hiccups during installation.</li><li>Consider making it a routine part of your Jeep maintenance to check and clean your door hinges regularly. This can help prevent the issues that led you to replace your liners in the first place.</li><li>Don’t force anything. If you encounter resistance during removal or installation, reassess instead of applying excessive pressure.</li></ul><h2>Key Takeaways</h2><p>Replacing your Jeep’s door hinge liners with TMR Customs Delrin bushings can significantly streamline door removal and combat corrosion issues. The ease of installation and the long-term benefits of using these bushings make them a worthwhile upgrade. With just a few tools and a little elbow grease, your Jeep doors can operate smoothly, restoring the ease of access that they should provide.</p>

